# The language-protocol fuzz corpus is binary (framed bytes — no UTF-8 seed is
# possible), so unlike the parser text seeds it is not tracked. The fuzzer
# regenerates coverage from scratch; the audit-integrity wording guard rejects
# tracked non-UTF-8 files.
